<exercise checkit-seed="0007" checkit-slug="F1" checkit-title="Simple Interest">
    <statement>
       
        
                <p>
                    Kabir loaned their friend $3,700. To make it easier on both of them, it is a simple interest loan with an annual interest rate of 14%. After 9 months have passed, they expect their friend to pay the loan back in one large payment.
                    <ol>
                        <li> How much interest does the loan generate over the 9 months? </li>
                        <li> How much will Kabir's friend have to pay at the end of the loan?</li>
                    </ol>
                </p>         
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li> The loan generates $388.5 in interest.</li>
                <li> They will need to pay $4,088.5 at the end of the loan.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
